Thousands of hectors of farmland have been destroyed by runaway fires in the Free State. Authorities say dozens of cattle and game have also been lost. To talk more about this, Jane Dutton speaks to Free State Agricultural Rural Safety Coordinator, André Van Rensburg. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A fire in the Free State is under control Thousands of hectares of land has been reduced to ash after two devastating infernos hit the province this week. READ: Farmer fighting for his life after runaway Free State fires Dozen of cattle and wild animals have also been lost. "At the moment we are trying to contain the fire," says Free State Agricultural Rural Safety Coordinator, André Van Rensburg. "After that, we will try determine the extent [of the impact]"